{
  "stem": "7358.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I remained there for a while, in the kibbutz, to pay my debts.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I worked full, full days to repay them for, for all the support and the food and, and the living quarters they gave me while I was going to school.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And at that point, they, they, they assigned me a job to, to, to-- the kibbutz-- all the kibbutzim had, like, a central management that was in Tel Aviv, that sort of helped all, all of them.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was like sort of a little-- like a little government of the kibbutzim, that any kind of problems that they had, they would call and they would seek help.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this was an organization that-- our, our organization had 48 kibbutzim.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a very major organization.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had-- the management of the kibbutz was in Tel Aviv.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And what did you have to do with that?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They assigned me a job to be a driver, because we had our own little, like, a ministry of transportation, because we needed-- we had 30 cars to serve the entire organization, because every time there was a problem, someone qualified had to go to assist the people with their problem.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was-- at that time, there was still a military problem, was safety problems.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a, it was a sort of a little self-sustaining organization.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I was assigned to be a driver.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And after a short period of time, the man that ran this, the 30-- the man in charge of the transportation became sick and he had to resign from his position.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they appointed me to be in charge of the group.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I lived-- we-- the kibbutz used to rent rooms for us in Tel Aviv.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
